2010-08-07  Charles Pence <charles@charlespence.net>

  * src/codegenerator.h, src/libjitformula.cpp, src/libjitformula.h,
  src/llvmformula.cpp, src/llvmformula.h, src/parsetree.h: Added a visitor
  pattern for the syntax tree for a CodeGenerator class.  The LLVMFormula and
  LibJITFormula classes are CodeGenerators.  The entire skeleton is now present
  to write JIT emission code.

  * README, build/m4/ax_boost_base.m4, config.h.in, configure.ac,
  src/parser.cpp, src/parser.h: Added much better error message formatting,
  which brings in a dependency on Boost.

  * src/jitformula.cpp, src/jitformula.h, src/parser.cpp, src/parser.h,
  src/parsetree.h, tests/test2.cpp: Of course, if the parser is global,
  everything breaks.  Right.  Stupid.  And fixed.

  * configure.ac, src/llvmformula.h: Fixed a few errors from the last build
  system change.

  * src/muparserformula.cpp, tests/test1.cpp, tests/test2.cpp: Updated the
  parser test to only test the parser; forcing the muParser code to parse to
  bytecode when setExpression is called.

  * build/m4/af_libjit.m4, build/m4/ax_llvm.m4, config.h.in, configure.ac,
  include/.gitignore, include/aformula.h, include/aformula.h.in,
  src/Makefile.am, src/formula.cpp, src/jitformula.cpp, src/jitformula.h,
  src/libjitformula.cpp, src/libjitformula.h, src/llvmformula.cpp,
  src/llvmformula.h: Doing a better job detecting libjit and llvm now, and
  compiling differentially based upon whether the two are available.

